summary: This script configures and runs a virtual machine using QEMU emulator. It checks if the latest version is needed, sets memory limits, selects serial port for communication, and executes the virtual machine.

details.comment: This script configures and runs a virtual machine using QEMU emulator. It checks if the latest version is needed, sets memory limits, selects serial port for communication, and executes the virtual machine.
details.content:
@echo off
REM do we need latest?
REM "D:\Program Files (x86)\Android\android-sdk\tools\qemu\windows-x86_64\qemu-system-x86_64.exe"  -enable-hax -m 2M,maxmem=5M -mem-path R:\ -hda c.hd -boot d
"E:\Program Files\qemu\qemu-system-x86_64.exe"  -accel hax -m 2M,slots=2,maxmem=5M  -nographic -serial COM4 -hda c.hd -boot d
